  "title": "refactor(components): share logic between refinement and menu components",
  "body": "> This is a big PR, mainly due to the types, snapshots and previously missing tests. I can try to split it in several PRs to make the review easier.\r\n\r\nThis refactors the widgets depending on the previous `RefinementList` component:\r\n\r\n- `RefinementList`\r\n- `HierarchicalMenu`\r\n- `Menu`\r\n- `NumericMenu`\r\n- `RatingMenu`\r\n\r\n## Impact\r\n\r\nIt will be easier to implement \"Show More\" and \"Search For Facet Values\" behaviors in their corresponding widgets.\r\n\r\nThey are also now typed with TypeScript.\r\n\r\n## Dependencies\r\n\r\nWe now have a main component called `List` that handles:\r\n\r\n- SearchBox\r\n- Facets display\r\n- No results display\r\n- Show more\r\n\r\nThis is the component that all other list widgets use.\r\n\r\n`HierarchicalMenu` and `SharedRefinementList` directely uses this `List` component. `SharedRefinementList` provides the primitives to build a refinement list experience. `Menu`, `NumericMenu` and `RatingMenu` use `SharedRefinementList`.\r\n\r\n```\r\n- List\r\n  - HierarchicalMenu\r\n  - SharedRefinementList\r\n    - RefinementList\r\n    - Menu\r\n    - NumericMenu\r\n    - RatingMenu\r\n```",
